Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, and low urine specific gravity, suggesting impaired renal function, possibly chronic kidney disease. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal odor) may indicate urinary tract pathology, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrite, leukocytes). Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes unlikely. Recommend nephrology evaluation and further workup for renal disease.
